definition: to spit/to send out (silk from a silkworm, bolls from cotton flowers etc)/to say/to pour out (one's grievances)

sentences.english: E. Bleed mixed with vomit or stool.
sentences.chinese: 嘔吐物含血或大便帶血。

sentences.english: Results There nitrite was detected from the gastric juice of the poisoning patients.
sentences.chinese: 結果在患者的洗胃液及嘔吐物中均檢出亞硝酸鹽。

sentences.english: The concentration of acid in vomitus or aspirate need not reach this limit .
sentences.chinese: 嘔吐物或吸引液內酸的濃度不需要達到這一程度。

sentences.english: But he also cleaned up vomit in police cars.
sentences.chinese: 但他也清理警車裏的嘔吐物。

sentences.english: Two of guards vomited and half a dozen cats got killed eating vomit.
sentences.chinese: 兩個獄卒嘔吐後半打貓咪去舔嘔吐物被殺。

sentences.english: Once this happens, blood appears in the vomit and faeces.
sentences.chinese: 一旦出現此種症狀，嘔吐物和糞便中就會帶血。

sentences.english: She choked on her vomit, Magill said.
sentences.chinese: Magill說，她因嘔吐物堵塞而窒息死亡。

sentences.english: He choked on his own vomit.
sentences.chinese: 他被自己的嘔吐物嗆住了。

sentences.english: Nothing is given by mouth, and the patient's head is turned to one side to avoid aspiration if emesis occurs.
sentences.chinese: 禁止口腔進食，病人頭部轉向一側以避免吸入嘔吐物。
